                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.5511/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-26T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>463. Your 294, July 23, noon.</p>
                <p>Please convey to the King the following message: “Having heard from Mr. Whitlock
                    that it might be possible for Your Majesty to come to this country for a short
                    time in the autumn I hasten to tender on behalf of the American Government a
                    most cordial invitation to Your Majesty and to Her Majesty the Queen of the
                    Belgians to visit the United States at such time as may best suit your
                    convenience.</p>
                <p>May I add a personal expression of the great pleasure that it will give me to
                    receive you and the Queen as the honored guests of the Nation. Woodrow
                    Wilson.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
